    {
      "id": "v_1772930748548_k08y",
      "title": "Jar video pilot episode 1",
      "statusId": "s2",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-08T00:45:48.548Z",
      "notes": [
        {
          "id": "n_1773103835533_b1z0",
          "text": "Open question is, since this is going to be a podcast with me talking by myself, my question is, how would I title this so that people know what it is? Do I say podcast in the title, episode one, so that people know this is like an ongoing series? Okay.",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-10T00:50:35.533Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "n_1773169391106_td74",
          "text": "The Jar is a weekly series where I sit down, pull random questions from a jar, and answer them honestly — no script, no filter, no right answers. Just me thinking out loud about life, identity, purpose, relationships, career, growth, and everything in between.\nIf you’re a young man trying to figure out who you are, what you want, and how to get there — this is the space. No guru energy. No motivational fluff. Just real reflection from someone still in the middle of figuring it out too.\nNew episodes drop weekly. Start anywhere — each one stands on its own.\nTags/keywords to include on the playlist:\npersonal growth, self-reflection, men’s mental health, life advice for young men, quarter life crisis, identity, purpose, real talk, journal prompts, deep questions, lifestyle, vulnerability, honest conversation, self-discovery, young men podcast",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-10T19:03:11.106Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "n_1773169488693_b2xd",
          "text": "The Jar | [##] — [Episode Subtitle / Best Question]\nI pulled [3-5] questions from the jar this week. Here’s what came up:\n🫙 [Question 1]\n🫙 [Question 2]\n🫙 [Question 3]\nNo script. No rehearsal. Just me sitting with whatever the jar throws at me and answering honestly.\nIf this one hit, drop a comment with a question you’d throw in the jar — I might answer it in a future episode.",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-10T19:04:48.693Z"
        }
      ],
