    {
      "id": "v_1772931532485_zg2i",
      "title": "ADHD diagnosed part 1",
      "statusId": "s2",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-08T00:58:52.485Z",
      "notes": [
        {
          "id": "n_1773106914316_gn6l",
          "text": "So the story goes like this: when I was a kid, I was diagnosed with ADHD. I took medication for a time, but then I kind of left it alone. I kind of went through life thinking that I didn't need it until I can't even remember right now, but I stumbled upon something where I'm like, \"Well, yeah, that's ADHD.\" I was at this place of healing my life and acknowledging a lot of things until I decided, \"Well, maybe it's time to look at that.\" I decided to really just focus on that. It's crazy because there's been so much healing from me acknowledging that I have it.",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-10T01:41:54.316Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "n_1773354411948_2qam",
          "text": "I think the way I'ma do this is I am gonna sit down, I'm gonna read my diagnosis, I'ma pull it up, and I really want to say what it means for me and in my life. I want to end with giving some people some tools and things of that nature.\n\nI want to sit down and talk about it. That's specifically what it means for me and what it's meant for me in my life and why I decided to do this. I want to come to the video of me putting it in for the first time, and then I want to cut back to myself in the present day to encourage people. I got to make sure I have a good segway for that cut part. I want to encourage people to go and get diagnosed if they are, and hopefully it helps people.\n\nI also want to have another segway for the second video where it's me actually going to an ADHD conference.",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-12T22:26:51.948Z"
        }
      ],
